{
  "text": "It is easy to see that Spec(Z) = {2} \u222a {\u221e}, and, for n \u2265 2, the spectrum of Z n is full, i.e. Spec(Z n ) = N \u222a {\u221e}. For free nilpotent groups we have the following: Spec(N 22 ) = 2N \u222a{\u221e} (N 22 is the discrete Heisenberg group) [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] ,",
